The paper introduces a new notion of pointwise coverage to measure the explainability properties of machine learning classifiers. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper investigates the most explainable classifier, which could also fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper's focus on explainability could also make it relevant to the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
